bility and reward for adventuring in these zones without completely remaking the contents of the zone. We plan to do several of these, and we'll keep you updated as we move through these. We recently finished Veeshan's Peak, the Temple of Droga and the mines of Nurga. Currently we are working on a partial revamps of The Deep, Charasis (Howling Stones), Dragon Necropolis, Sirens Grotto, The Hole, The City of Mist, Cazic-Thule, and Velketor's Labyrinth. <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
I think cazic thule is pretty good as it is, if it turns blue again.  The xp was shot and did not reflect difficulty after pop went live.  <br>
<br>
Actually, many of these zones were GREAT xp for a solid group of the right level, back in the day, or even now.  Granted, some of them are not too accessible or just plain unforgiving if you don't have an evac and enchanter.<br>
<br>
I wonder what will change.  I vote fewer harm touches.<br>
<br>
We'll have to keep an eye on CoM for the concussion quest.<br>
<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=seaotter42>SeaOtter42</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br>  Posts: 304<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/5/03 12:47 pm)</font><br>     <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Upcoming partial zone revamps</span><hr size=1> The Deep, Charasis (Howling Stones), Dragon Necropolis, are all great canditates for re-vamps. <br>
<br>
City of Mist is a mixed bag... since its primarily only hunted for epic drops. The layout of the city would allow it to be a really neat high end zone, but something would have to be done with the epic pieces that are obtained there currently (Shaman, SK, Enchanter, Mage, Druid, Ranger that I know of).<br>
<br>
Sirens Grotto, The Hole, Cazic-Thule, and Velketor's Labyrinth are all great zones as it is... I wish they'd leave some of the better zones alone and fix other places first. I still don't care for the hateplane change, as in its old form it was a fantastic zone to introduce lower level characters to raiding.<br>
<br>
Wheres Plane of Mischief on this list? How about Griegs End? Ahkeva Ruins? Plane of Sky?<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=zupe>Zupe</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Arcanist<BR>User Interface Prodigy</span><br>  Posts: 901<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/5/03 2:24 pm)</font><br>     <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Upcoming partial zone revamps</span><hr size=1> PoM has been revamped more than once in theory over the last year. It was supposed to go live with PoP and yet we still see it as a broken zone. I don't know if we will ever see it fixed.<br>
<br>
I would love HS to be revamped, that was a cool zone and had so much potential. DN is still fun to those pre-65 so I am unsure if I would change it a lot. The new Veskar kind of sucks if you ask me. Green mobs that summon and hit for 175 are just not that fun to play with. <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=18567" target="top"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.kkeele.com/EQ/zupesig.jpg" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=18567" target="top">Zupe Blastemded</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
</div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=erumaroneverbright>Erumaron Everbright</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Channeler</span><br>  Posts: 248<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/5/03 2:28 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Upcoming partial zone revamps</span><hr size=1> Griegs End is great as is..I love that zone.  Akeva is fine too eh. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=whizbangdustyboots>Whizbang Dustyboots</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elder Arcanist<BR>Gnomus Originalus</span><br>  Posts: 13167<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/5/03 7:11 pm)</font><br>     <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Upcoming partial zone revamps</span><hr size=1> Grieg's End is a one joke sitcom. After you hear that joke once, hearing it again and again and again for the next hour as you clear to the named you're going to kill, it gets to be very shallow content.<br>
<br>
Add to the fact that the regular drops have been massively nerfed. (My guild has been killing Grieg and Servitor of late -- with massive deaths of the yard trash, 0 beer goggles have dropped, nor have any other items, like the 2hb broom.)<br>
<br>
Grieg's could certainly stand a content infusion. <p><a href="http://www.EQPixelArmy.com" target="_blank"><img src="http://www.lby3.com/eq/whiz/whiz-animated-banner-animation.gif" height="120" width="80" alt="EQPA" border=0></a><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=41790" target="_blank"><img src="http://www.lby3.com/eq/whiz/whiz-animated-banner-text.gif" height=120 width=272 alt="Whizbang Dustyboots" border=0></a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=jadrax>Jadrax</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Arcanist</span><br>  Posts: 1386<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/6/03 3:25 am)</font><br>     <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> ...</span><hr size=1> Kerra Island is I think the number one useless EQ zone now.<br>
<br>
After that the list is pretty long.<br>
<br>
Permafrost is probably the second most in need of a revamp. <br>
<br>
As for the rest of the old world zones Mistmoor, Kithicor, Upper Guk, Najena, dagnor's Cauldren all need a revamp as there pretty pointless now.<br>
<br>
Kunark zones are better but, Dalnir, Emeral jungle, Kaesora, Swamp of no Hope all need a revamp. (not counting droga/nurga as they are being revamped now)<br>
<br>
Velious - Dragon necropolis, eastern wastes, iceclad, wakening and western wastes could use a revamp.<br>
