<br>
PoP - This is all pretty well used right now.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=zertez>zertez</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 164<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/6/03 4:11 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>  ...</span><hr size=1>  It is a scary thought what SOE's definition for partial is given what they consider finished products. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=quineloe>Quineloe</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Arcanist</span><br>  Posts: 1824<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/6/03 5:04 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re:  ...</span><hr size=1> dont worry zertez, partial means they are only breaking half of the content of the zone <p>Sage Quineloe<br>
